The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  dropped 0.1 percent to 19,360.66.
The  MSCI All Peru Capped Index  fell 0.2 percent to 2,502.35.  Mining stocks retreated after gold, silver and zinc futures
declined, said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, fell 10 percent to 9 cents.  Panoro Minerals
Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian gold and copper exploration company,
slid 2.8 percent to 35 cents.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN) 
, the countryâ€™s biggest precious-metals miner, dropped
0.9 percent to $39.35.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian
company with a mine in Peru, dropped 0.6 percent to $3.17.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 1.9 percent to $1.10
after crude gained for a third day in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
